Steps:
1) Follow Elisha's ReadMe.md file first.
2) Install Node.js, check the command below in PowerShell 
node -v 
npm -v

3) Get the project files clone/download from Github. [Example: C:\xampp\htdocs\BAIT2123-Internet-of-Things-GymSense-Gym-System]
4) Open PowerShell in the project folder and run -> cd C:\xampp\htdocs\BAIT2123-Internet-of-Things-GymSense-Gym-System
5) Install the project packages and run > npm install

*IF PowerShell blocks npm*
If you get the “running scripts is disabled” error, run this first in the same PowerShell window:
> Set-ExecutionPolicy -Scope Process -ExecutionPolicy Bypass
Then, run
>npm install

6) Open the Firebase project
   Project Name: Gymsensor

7) Inside Firebase Console > Build → Realtime Database 

Copy the database URL. It should look like this:
https://gymsensor-ce1ec-default-rtdb.asia-southeast1.firebasedatabase.app/

8) In Firebase Console>  Project settings → Service accounts → Generate new private key

Save it in the project folder, for example:
C:\xampp\htdocs\BAIT2123-Internet-of-Things-GymSense-Gym-System\serviceAccountKey.json

9) In PowerShell, inside the project folder, run: [Very Important!]

$env:GOOGLE_APPLICATION_CREDENTIALS="C:\xampp\htdocs\BAIT2123-Internet-of-Things-GymSense-Gym-System\serviceAccountKey.json"
$env:FIREBASE_DATABASE_URL="https://gymsensor-ce1ec-default-rtdb.asia-southeast1.firebasedatabase.app/"

10) Start the server run > node server.js
will get something like this:

http://localhost:3000

11) To check whether access works or not 

Open in browser:
http://localhost:3000/control
http://localhost:3000/workout

12) Open the website frontend

Every time open a new PowerShell window, must to set these two lines again before running node server.js:

$env:GOOGLE_APPLICATION_CREDENTIALS="C:\xampp\htdocs\BAIT2123-Internet-of-Things-GymSense-Gym-System\serviceAccountKey.json"
$env:FIREBASE_DATABASE_URL="https://gymsensor-ce1ec-default-rtdb.asia-southeast1.firebasedatabase.app/"

13) Common problems!!!: 

If npm install is blocked:
Set-ExecutionPolicy -Scope Process -ExecutionPolicy Bypass

If port 3000 is already in use, it usually means another Node server is already running. Close the old one with Ctrl + C first.

If Firebase access fails, double-check:
-the JSON key file path
-the database URL
-does inside the correct project folder
-are using the same PowerShell window where the env vars were set





